  <eligibility>
    <study_pop>
      <textblock>
        Adult patients (18-60 years) scheduled for routine nasal and/or paranasal sinus surgeries
        in Ankara Univerity Faculty of Medicine, ETN operating rooms were recruited into this
        study.
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  18-60 years old adult patient

          -  nasal and/or paranasal sinus surgeries

          -  general anesthesia

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  patients submitted to another intervention at the same time (adenoidectomy,
             tonsillectomy)

          -  patients with a serious systemic disease (acquired immunodeficiency syndrome,leukemia,
             lymphoma, or other neoplasias under chemotherapy treatment)

          -  patients presenting contraindications for using nonsteroid anti-inflammatory drugs
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
    <gender>All</gender>
